WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:29.863 --> 00:00:32.198 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
My name is Ryoma Takebayashi.

00:00:32.282 --> 00:00:34.701 position:50% align:center
I'm your typical 11-year-old
living in the forest

00:00:34.784 --> 00:00:36.536 position:50% align:center
where it's just me,
myself, and I,

00:00:36.619 --> 00:00:37.996 position:50% align:center
day in and day out.

00:00:38.079 --> 00:00:40.790 position:50% align:center
Oh. But I guess I'm
not entirely alone.

00:00:43.084 --> 00:00:46.046 position:50% align:center
I also live with nearly
a thousand slimes!

00:00:46.129 --> 00:00:47.255 position:50% align:center
Minor detail.

00:00:51.468 --> 00:00:54.637 position:50% align:center
Slimes evolve differently
depending on what you feed them.

00:00:54.721 --> 00:00:57.515 position:50% align:center
For instance, I fed green
caterpillars to some of them

00:00:57.599 --> 00:00:59.559 position:50% align:center
and they turned into
sticky slimes.

00:01:02.312 --> 00:01:04.481 position:50% align:center
The sticky fluid they form
inside their bodies

00:01:04.564 --> 00:01:06.483 position:50% align:center
can be used to make
a powerful thread

00:01:06.566 --> 00:01:09.944 position:50% align:center
that comes in pretty handy
for hunting and stuff.

00:01:10.028 --> 00:01:11.529 position:50% align:center
Acid slimes, on the other hand,

00:01:11.613 --> 00:01:13.990 position:50% align:center
have highly acidic bodily
fluids that are capable

00:01:14.074 --> 00:01:17.035 position:50% align:center
of dissolving hard
things like bones.

00:01:17.118 --> 00:01:19.120 position:50% align:center
And these resilient little
guys made the mistake

00:01:19.204 --> 00:01:21.831 position:50% align:center
of eating toxic weeds,
yet managed to survive,

00:01:21.915 --> 00:01:23.917 position:50% align:center
so now they're poison slimes.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:25.543 position:50% align:center
Considering how much
faster they split

00:01:25.627 --> 00:01:29.047 position:50% align:center
compared to other types,
their vitality's no joke.

00:01:29.130 --> 00:01:31.925 position:50% align:center
Cleaner slimes clean things
by eating dirt and grime.

00:01:32.008 --> 00:01:35.512 position:50% align:center
And get this, they even
eliminate smells!

00:01:35.595 --> 00:01:38.431 position:50% align:center
Scavenger slimes consume
excrement and garbage,

00:01:38.515 --> 00:01:40.767 position:50% align:center
which sounds gross,
but they create fertilizer.

00:01:58.493 --> 00:01:59.619 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah.

00:01:59.703 --> 00:02:01.413 position:50% align:center
I guess I do run into
goblins and thieves

00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:03.081 position:50% align:center
from time to time
and have no choice

00:02:03.164 --> 00:02:04.582 position:50% align:center
but to defend myself.

00:02:07.168 --> 00:02:10.213 position:50% align:center
For the most part, though,
every day is nice and peaceful.

00:02:11.256 --> 00:02:13.341 position:50% align:center
[REINHART]
Don't you die, Hughes!

00:02:13.425 --> 00:02:14.843 position:50% align:center
--[CAMIL] Hughes!
--[ZEPH] Please!

00:02:14.926 --> 00:02:16.845 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA] I thought my simple
way of life with the slimes

00:02:16.928 --> 00:02:19.264 position:50% align:center
in the forest would
last forever.

00:02:19.347 --> 00:02:21.641 position:50% align:center
But I suppose I should
expect the unexpected

00:02:21.725 --> 00:02:22.934 position:50% align:center
from time to time.

00:04:00.990 --> 00:04:03.243 position:50% align:center
They don't look like bandits.

00:04:03.326 --> 00:04:04.744 position:50% align:center
But I have to wonder
what they're doing

00:04:04.828 --> 00:04:06.329 position:50% align:center
this deep in the forest.

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:11.960 position:50% align:center
Is it bad?

00:04:12.043 --> 00:04:13.545 position:50% align:center
It isn't good.

00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:17.298 position:50% align:center
It's gonna take magic to heal
him, and I don't have enough.

00:04:17.382 --> 00:04:19.968 position:50% align:center
Then we should hurry and get
him back to town.

00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:21.928 position:50% align:center
He won't last much longer.

00:04:22.012 --> 00:04:23.096 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
Umm...

00:04:27.142 --> 00:04:28.143 position:50% align:center
Who are you?

00:04:28.226 --> 00:04:31.104 position:50% align:center
Um... I, uh, um uh...

00:04:31.187 --> 00:04:33.982 position:50% align:center
Why's he here? He's just a kid.

00:04:34.065 --> 00:04:35.817 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA] I guess my voice is
rusty since I haven't had

00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:37.652 position:50% align:center
to use it in years.

00:04:37.736 --> 00:04:39.320 position:50% align:center
[clears throat]

00:04:39.404 --> 00:04:42.115 position:50% align:center
Medicine. Me give you.

00:04:42.198 --> 00:04:44.284 position:50% align:center
Why am I talking like a caveman?

00:04:44.367 --> 00:04:45.368 position:50% align:center
Medicine?

00:04:46.745 --> 00:04:50.623 position:50% align:center
Right here. You take. Hurry.

00:05:05.638 --> 00:05:06.765 position:50% align:center
[REINHART]
Well?

00:05:06.848 --> 00:05:08.058 position:50% align:center
Hughes is in luck!

00:05:08.141 --> 00:05:09.601 position:50% align:center
I'm positive it's medicine.

00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:18.360 position:50% align:center
Is he...?

00:05:18.443 --> 00:05:19.903 position:50% align:center
[CAMIL]
He just fell asleep.

00:05:19.986 --> 00:05:21.529 position:50% align:center
This ought to sustain
him for a while.

00:05:23.073 --> 00:05:24.574 position:50% align:center
Thank you, boy.

00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:29.245 position:50% align:center
My home. Can rest. All of you.

00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:30.330 position:50% align:center
You're sure?

00:05:32.832 --> 00:05:34.751 position:50% align:center
What's a little kid like
him doing in a forest

00:05:34.834 --> 00:05:36.378 position:50% align:center
all by himself?

00:05:36.461 --> 00:05:38.880 position:50% align:center
We don't know if he's
alone just yet.

00:05:38.963 --> 00:05:40.173 position:50% align:center
I'd wager he's a hunter.

00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:43.051 position:50% align:center
What's wrong?

00:05:43.134 --> 00:05:46.221 position:50% align:center
Seems beast came this way.
So they'll come, too.

00:05:46.304 --> 00:05:47.514 position:50% align:center
[CAMIL]
Who's "they?"

00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:49.182 position:50% align:center
[SLIMES jiggle]

00:05:50.892 --> 00:05:52.727 position:50% align:center
Those slimes came
out of nowhere!

00:05:52.811 --> 00:05:54.729 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA gasps]

00:05:54.813 --> 00:05:56.356 position:50% align:center
Enemy! They're not!

00:05:58.817 --> 00:06:00.860 position:50% align:center
Wait, are you trying to tell
us that those slimes

00:06:00.944 --> 00:06:02.153 position:50% align:center
are actually your servants?

00:06:07.992 --> 00:06:09.619 position:50% align:center
My apologies, then.

00:06:09.703 --> 00:06:11.871 position:50% align:center
None of us realized that
they were your familiars.

00:06:16.751 --> 00:06:19.045 position:50% align:center
I used to have slimes
for familiars.

00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:20.463 position:50% align:center
My very first ones.

00:06:20.547 --> 00:06:22.465 position:50% align:center
I remember it like
it was yesterday.

00:06:22.549 --> 00:06:24.384 position:50% align:center
That mean you tamer?

00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:27.929 position:50% align:center
Former. But, yes.
Runs in my family.

00:06:28.013 --> 00:06:30.056 position:50% align:center
We've been tamers
for generations.

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:31.891 position:50% align:center
But slimes weren't
my only familiars.

00:06:31.975 --> 00:06:34.978 position:50% align:center
We had red horses and
blizzard apes, primarily.

00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:36.563 position:50% align:center
Ah...

00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:37.981 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
So he's a noble.

00:06:38.064 --> 00:06:39.899 position:50% align:center
Maybe even an important one.

00:06:44.404 --> 00:06:46.281 position:50% align:center
Looks like a dead end to me.

00:06:46.364 --> 00:06:47.907 position:50% align:center
Maybe he got lost?

00:06:47.991 --> 00:06:49.534 position:50% align:center
Wait, please. Thank you.

00:06:56.791 --> 00:06:58.835 position:50% align:center
This home.

00:06:58.918 --> 00:07:00.420 position:50% align:center
Barrier magic, huh?

00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:02.005 position:50% align:center
To keep this place hidden.

00:07:02.088 --> 00:07:03.089 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:07:06.051 --> 00:07:07.886 position:50% align:center
I've never seen
a cave this cozy.

00:07:07.969 --> 00:07:09.095 position:50% align:center
Same.

00:07:09.179 --> 00:07:10.805 position:50% align:center
What are the odds we'd
find a decent place

00:07:10.889 --> 00:07:12.015 position:50% align:center
for Hughes to rest?

00:07:12.098 --> 00:07:14.267 position:50% align:center
You say decent,
but I say suspicious.

00:07:14.351 --> 00:07:15.810 position:50% align:center
What? How so?

00:07:15.894 --> 00:07:18.605 position:50% align:center
There's only enough
furniture for one person.

00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:20.607 position:50% align:center
[REINHART]
Huh. That's true.

00:07:20.690 --> 00:07:22.984 position:50% align:center
It appears he does, indeed,
live here alone.

00:07:23.068 --> 00:07:24.110 position:50% align:center
Seriously?

00:07:24.194 --> 00:07:25.779 position:50% align:center
Earlier, when he approached us.

00:07:25.862 --> 00:07:28.281 position:50% align:center
he masked his presence
remarkably well.

00:07:28.365 --> 00:07:30.992 position:50% align:center
His magic also makes me
think he may not be

00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:32.660 position:50% align:center
as young as he looks.

00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:38.041 position:50% align:center
This for hurt man.

00:07:38.124 --> 00:07:39.417 position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:07:39.501 --> 00:07:41.586 position:50% align:center
I promise we'll find
a way to repay you.

00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:44.673 position:50% align:center
No. Take all you like.
Can make more.

00:07:44.756 --> 00:07:46.466 position:50% align:center
You made them? Wow.

00:07:46.549 --> 00:07:48.968 position:50% align:center
They're potions!
You really made these?

00:07:49.052 --> 00:07:50.178 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
Uh, yes.

00:07:50.261 --> 00:07:52.222 position:50% align:center
[REINHART]
Hmm. What are you?

00:07:52.305 --> 00:07:54.474 position:50% align:center
I, um... Oh, right!

00:07:54.557 --> 00:07:57.435 position:50% align:center
You have thirst? Here.

00:07:57.519 --> 00:07:58.645 position:50% align:center
[CAMIL]
Ice?

00:07:58.728 --> 00:08:01.106 position:50% align:center
[JILL] You're capable
of using ice magic?

00:08:01.189 --> 00:08:02.941 position:50% align:center
Please tell us who you are.

00:08:03.024 --> 00:08:05.318 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
Jeez, they sure are persistent.

00:08:05.402 --> 00:08:08.613 position:50% align:center
My, um... My name is Ryoma.

00:08:08.697 --> 00:08:11.074 position:50% align:center
Thanks for your help, Ryoma.

00:08:11.157 --> 00:08:13.910 position:50% align:center
Since you told me your name,
I'll tell you mine.

00:08:13.993 --> 00:08:16.329 position:50% align:center
I'm Reinhart Jamil
of the Jamil Duchy.

00:08:16.413 --> 00:08:17.706 position:50% align:center
He say Duchy?!

00:08:17.789 --> 00:08:19.749 position:50% align:center
Uh... uh, forgive me!

00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:22.127 position:50% align:center
There's no need to bow down
to me, I assure you.

00:08:22.210 --> 00:08:24.462 position:50% align:center
Especially since
I'm in your debt.

00:08:24.546 --> 00:08:26.423 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
Uh, okay.

00:08:26.506 --> 00:08:30.343 position:50% align:center
I figured he was probably a big
deal, but not a duke-sized deal!

00:08:30.427 --> 00:08:32.887 position:50% align:center
Nice to meet you,
my name is Camil.

00:08:32.971 --> 00:08:34.264 position:50% align:center
I'm a mage.

00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:35.932 position:50% align:center
Though I didn't have enough
magic to heal Hughes,

00:08:36.016 --> 00:08:37.600 position:50% align:center
so I'm glad you came along.

00:08:37.684 --> 00:08:39.728 position:50% align:center
I'm grateful to you
as well, kid.

00:08:39.811 --> 00:08:41.855 position:50% align:center
I'm a scout. Name's Zeph.

00:08:41.938 --> 00:08:43.273 position:50% align:center
I'm Jill.

00:08:43.356 --> 00:08:45.525 position:50% align:center
And I'm sorry for drawing
my sword on you.

00:08:45.608 --> 00:08:49.404 position:50% align:center
Caution is natural.
No apology.

00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:51.448 position:50% align:center
Thanks.
That's kind of you to say.

00:08:51.531 --> 00:08:53.783 position:50% align:center
So, uh... How did...

00:08:53.867 --> 00:08:56.494 position:50% align:center
Outside the forest,
we were struck by bandits.

00:08:56.578 --> 00:08:57.912 position:50% align:center
They hurt your friend?

00:08:57.996 --> 00:08:59.039 position:50% align:center
No.

00:08:59.122 --> 00:09:00.999 position:50% align:center
We took the bandits
out easily enough.

00:09:01.082 --> 00:09:03.418 position:50% align:center
But then a black bear
also came after us.

00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:04.919 position:50% align:center
Ah, gotcha.

00:09:05.003 --> 00:09:07.422 position:50% align:center
We managed to beat
the black bear, too.

00:09:07.505 --> 00:09:09.841 position:50% align:center
But not before
our horses ran away.

00:09:09.924 --> 00:09:12.135 position:50% align:center
We wanted to get Hughes
to town as fast as we could,

00:09:12.218 --> 00:09:14.429 position:50% align:center
so we took a shortcut
through the forest.

00:09:14.512 --> 00:09:15.847 position:50% align:center
Then we bumped into you.

00:09:15.930 --> 00:09:17.015 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
Hm.

00:09:17.098 --> 00:09:19.059 position:50% align:center
Can I ask you a question,
too, Ryoma?

00:09:19.142 --> 00:09:20.602 position:50% align:center
Uh... O-Okay.

00:09:20.685 --> 00:09:24.773 position:50% align:center
You wield different magics.
And you create your own potions.

00:09:24.856 --> 00:09:26.775 position:50% align:center
Why live out here
with such talents?

00:09:26.858 --> 00:09:28.318 position:50% align:center
Um... I, uh...

00:09:30.278 --> 00:09:32.447 position:50% align:center
My grandparents
taught me those things.

00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:34.699 position:50% align:center
They were adventurers.

00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:36.409 position:50% align:center
I see.

00:09:36.493 --> 00:09:39.788 position:50% align:center
And I take it they're
just out right now?

00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:42.582 position:50% align:center
Three years ago, they both died.

00:09:42.665 --> 00:09:44.167 position:50% align:center
[REINHART]
Three years?

00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:46.252 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA] They said that I should
try and go to another village.

00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:49.339 position:50% align:center
Those were their
dying words to me.

00:09:49.422 --> 00:09:51.091 position:50% align:center
But I couldn't do that.

00:09:51.174 --> 00:09:54.552 position:50% align:center
Villagers don't trust outsiders.

00:09:54.636 --> 00:09:57.472 position:50% align:center
That much, I understand.
Certainly.

00:09:57.555 --> 00:10:00.475 position:50% align:center
Grasping how you survived
is where I'm troubled.

00:10:00.558 --> 00:10:03.687 position:50% align:center
For three years,
I just lived from day to day.

00:10:03.770 --> 00:10:04.771 position:50% align:center
You "just lived?"

00:10:04.854 --> 00:10:07.565 position:50% align:center
Hey, guys! I know!

00:10:07.649 --> 00:10:09.025 position:50% align:center
Let's use this crystal!

00:10:09.109 --> 00:10:11.736 position:50% align:center
It shines bright red any time
a criminal touches it.

00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:13.822 position:50% align:center
For everybody else,
it shines blue.

00:10:13.905 --> 00:10:14.906 position:50% align:center
Oh.

00:10:14.989 --> 00:10:16.449 position:50% align:center
That's not all.

00:10:16.533 --> 00:10:18.451 position:50% align:center
It shows their name,
race, and age, too.

00:10:18.535 --> 00:10:20.245 position:50% align:center
It also has the power
to reveal four of their

00:10:20.328 --> 00:10:22.288 position:50% align:center
high-level skillsets.

00:10:22.372 --> 00:10:23.957 position:50% align:center
No one would second-guess
you living alone

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:26.001 position:50% align:center
in the forest if we knew
you had a high enough

00:10:26.084 --> 00:10:28.169 position:50% align:center
combat skill to
fend for yourself.

00:10:28.253 --> 00:10:31.798 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
Makes sense.

00:10:31.881 --> 00:10:34.175 position:50% align:center
It's blue!
Which means you're no criminal.

00:10:36.344 --> 00:10:37.470 position:50% align:center
But what's this?

00:10:37.554 --> 00:10:38.847 position:50% align:center
Uh... What's what?

00:10:38.930 --> 00:10:41.224 position:50% align:center
Uh... Well, uh...

00:10:41.307 --> 00:10:42.475 position:50% align:center
According to this thing,

00:10:42.559 --> 00:10:44.519 position:50% align:center
you don't have any
combat skills.

00:10:44.602 --> 00:10:46.521 position:50% align:center
Aw. Shucks.

00:10:46.604 --> 00:10:49.357 position:50% align:center
Anyway, I'll go ahead
and get dinner ready.

00:10:49.441 --> 00:10:50.525 position:50% align:center
[REINHART]
Sounds good.

00:10:51.401 --> 00:10:53.194 position:50% align:center
You need to see this.

00:10:53.278 --> 00:10:55.113 position:50% align:center
Age 11?

00:10:55.196 --> 00:10:57.323 position:50% align:center
That would mean
he's been alone since

00:10:57.407 --> 00:10:59.034 position:50% align:center
he was eight years old.

00:10:59.117 --> 00:11:02.495 position:50% align:center
While that is a surprising fact,
look at the skills.

00:11:02.579 --> 00:11:04.914 position:50% align:center
Housekeeping, level ten.

00:11:04.998 --> 00:11:07.751 position:50% align:center
And he's level nine for
mental pain resistance.

00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:10.795 position:50% align:center
Followed by physical pain
resistance at level eight!

00:11:10.879 --> 00:11:13.256 position:50% align:center
He's only a kid,
but what kind of life

00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:15.091 position:50% align:center
has he been living?

00:11:15.175 --> 00:11:18.094 position:50% align:center
All I know is we can't leave
him here by himself.

00:11:18.178 --> 00:11:21.431 position:50% align:center
That said, what actions
do we take?

00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:22.724 position:50% align:center
My gut's telling me

00:11:22.807 --> 00:11:24.267 position:50% align:center
I should head home
and discuss this matter

00:11:24.351 --> 00:11:25.894 position:50% align:center
with Father and Elise.

00:11:27.562 --> 00:11:29.189 position:50% align:center
[HUGHES grunts]

00:11:29.272 --> 00:11:31.316 position:50% align:center
Thanks for saving me,
little guy!

00:11:31.399 --> 00:11:33.777 position:50% align:center
Feel better? You sure?

00:11:33.860 --> 00:11:36.654 position:50% align:center
Oh-ho!
That genuine concern I hear?

00:11:36.738 --> 00:11:39.074 position:50% align:center
I have it on good authority
you avoid the town.

00:11:39.157 --> 00:11:41.117 position:50% align:center
I thought it was because
you didn't like people, but...

00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:42.410 position:50% align:center
[CAMIL]
Hughes!

00:11:42.494 --> 00:11:45.497 position:50% align:center
Even so, I still worry when
someone gets hurt.

00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:46.748 position:50% align:center
[HUGHES laughs]

00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:49.959 position:50% align:center
I guess avoiding isn't
synonymous with dislik--

00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:51.211 position:50% align:center
Hughes. You good?

00:11:51.294 --> 00:11:52.712 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah. Just dandy.

00:11:52.796 --> 00:11:55.256 position:50% align:center
Missing a few pints
of blood, but it's fine.

00:11:55.340 --> 00:11:57.884 position:50% align:center
Drink this. It'll restore blood.

00:11:57.967 --> 00:12:00.929 position:50% align:center
Thank you! Don't mind if I do.

00:12:01.012 --> 00:12:02.472 position:50% align:center
It smells awful!

00:12:02.555 --> 00:12:05.392 position:50% align:center
But it works! I guarantee it.

00:12:05.475 --> 00:12:06.476 position:50% align:center
[HUGHES]
Uh...!

00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:08.561 position:50% align:center
Don't refuse his kindness.
Drink it.

00:12:08.645 --> 00:12:10.939 position:50% align:center
Can't have you collapsing
on the road, now can we?

00:12:11.022 --> 00:12:13.024 position:50% align:center
We're all very concerned
for you and only thinking

00:12:13.108 --> 00:12:14.150 position:50% align:center
of your health.

00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:15.485 position:50% align:center
[CAMIL]
Bottoms up!

00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:20.323 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:12:20.407 --> 00:12:21.950 position:50% align:center
I want you to listen to me.

00:12:22.033 --> 00:12:24.160 position:50% align:center
Remember this, okay?

00:12:24.244 --> 00:12:25.578 position:50% align:center
My name's Hughes
and I'm bodyguard

00:12:25.662 --> 00:12:27.163 position:50% align:center
to the duke of Jamil.

00:12:27.247 --> 00:12:29.624 position:50% align:center
If you ever need help,
you march right into the town

00:12:29.708 --> 00:12:31.584 position:50% align:center
of Ganago and ask for me.

00:12:31.668 --> 00:12:34.629 position:50% align:center
That way I can return the favor!
You hear me?

00:12:36.172 --> 00:12:37.340 position:50% align:center
Loud 'n' clear!

00:12:38.550 --> 00:12:40.844 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
They were really nice people.

00:12:40.927 --> 00:12:43.013 position:50% align:center
Makes me feel
all the more guilty.

00:12:43.096 --> 00:12:45.557 position:50% align:center
Nice people don't
deserve to be lied to,

00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:48.018 position:50% align:center
but that's exactly what I did.

00:12:48.101 --> 00:12:50.645 position:50% align:center
I made up that entire story
about my grandparents

00:12:50.729 --> 00:12:52.355 position:50% align:center
passing away.

00:12:52.439 --> 00:12:55.525 position:50% align:center
The person who actually
died three years ago

00:12:55.608 --> 00:12:56.693 position:50% align:center
was me.

00:12:58.903 --> 00:13:00.739 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA] There'll be many
more slimes to come!

00:13:03.491 --> 00:13:05.910 position:50% align:center
The view is nice,
but how do I get down?

00:13:07.746 --> 00:13:10.457 position:50% align:center
[MANAGER]
How big of an idiot can you be?

00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:13.043 position:50% align:center
Are you seriously not done?

00:13:13.126 --> 00:13:16.254 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
This is me three years ago.

00:13:16.338 --> 00:13:18.590 position:50% align:center
You might've noticed,
but I was a tiny bit older

00:13:18.673 --> 00:13:20.258 position:50% align:center
than I am now.

00:13:20.342 --> 00:13:22.302 position:50% align:center
The place I lived was
also a little different

00:13:22.385 --> 00:13:25.055 position:50% align:center
compared to my current home.

00:13:25.138 --> 00:13:28.933 position:50% align:center
One day I found myself
in a strange place.

00:13:30.018 --> 00:13:32.687 position:50% align:center
So. I really worked
myself to death.

00:13:32.771 --> 00:13:33.980 position:50% align:center
I see.

00:13:34.773 --> 00:13:36.066 position:50% align:center
You for real?

00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:38.443 position:50% align:center
You are taking the news
surprisingly well.

00:13:38.526 --> 00:13:40.195 position:50% align:center
Most folks who come here
are much more upset

00:13:40.278 --> 00:13:41.946 position:50% align:center
by this revelation.

00:13:42.030 --> 00:13:44.157 position:50% align:center
But you don't seem
fazed in the slightest.

00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:47.035 position:50% align:center
I assure you, I'm surprised.
It's just...

00:13:47.118 --> 00:13:50.038 position:50% align:center
I'll eventually wake up if
this turns out to be a dream.

00:13:50.121 --> 00:13:53.667 position:50% align:center
If not, everybody's lives
have to end at some point.

00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:54.834 position:50% align:center
And besides...

00:13:54.918 --> 00:13:57.045 position:50% align:center
I knew my job would
be the death of me.

00:13:57.128 --> 00:14:00.131 position:50% align:center
It was only a matter
of time, honestly.

00:14:00.215 --> 00:14:03.343 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA] I worked for a horribly
exploitative company.

00:14:03.426 --> 00:14:07.555 position:50% align:center
Massive overtime.
Terrible bosses. No days off.

00:14:07.639 --> 00:14:09.933 position:50% align:center
So I was perpetually exhausted.

00:14:10.016 --> 00:14:12.102 position:50% align:center
Now that I'm thinking of it,
who are you?

00:14:12.185 --> 00:14:13.311 position:50% align:center
[GAIN]
We're gods.

00:14:13.395 --> 00:14:14.562 position:50% align:center
Huh.

00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:17.941 position:50% align:center
Refer to me as Gain the Creator.
Short 'n' sweet.

00:14:18.024 --> 00:14:20.902 position:50% align:center
I'm Lulutia,
the Goddess of Love.

00:14:20.985 --> 00:14:23.822 position:50% align:center
I'm the God of Life, Kufo.

00:14:23.905 --> 00:14:25.782 position:50% align:center
I am honored to meet
all three of you.

00:14:25.865 --> 00:14:28.159 position:50% align:center
My name is Ryoma Takebayashi.

00:14:28.243 --> 00:14:29.452 position:50% align:center
But please, forgive me.

00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:31.913 position:50% align:center
Usually, I have a few
business cards on hand.

00:14:31.996 --> 00:14:33.289 position:50% align:center
We don't need that.

00:14:33.373 --> 00:14:35.166 position:50% align:center
The world we live in is much
different from the one

00:14:35.250 --> 00:14:37.002 position:50% align:center
you come from, so we
would have no use

00:14:37.085 --> 00:14:38.712 position:50% align:center
for such trivial things.

00:14:38.795 --> 00:14:41.047 position:50% align:center
[TAKEBAYASHI]
Ah. Like an "other world," yeah?

00:14:41.131 --> 00:14:43.800 position:50% align:center
So did you attain enlightenment
while you were still alive?

00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:45.802 position:50% align:center
It's actually quite nice
to not have to explain

00:14:45.885 --> 00:14:47.554 position:50% align:center
every little thing for once.

00:14:47.637 --> 00:14:50.890 position:50% align:center
[TAKEBAYASHI] It's a concept you
see a lot in manga and anime.

00:14:50.974 --> 00:14:52.017 position:50% align:center
It's just...

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:53.309 position:50% align:center
[GAIN]
Just what?

00:14:53.393 --> 00:14:55.729 position:50% align:center
I can't help but be curious
as to how I died.

00:14:55.812 --> 00:14:57.731 position:50% align:center
You hit your head and
had a brain hemorrhage.

00:14:57.814 --> 00:14:59.441 position:50% align:center
Sorry if that's disappointing.

00:14:59.524 --> 00:15:01.651 position:50% align:center
That's right. It was the
result of you sneezing

00:15:01.735 --> 00:15:04.154 position:50% align:center
while you were sleeping.
Four in a row.

00:15:04.237 --> 00:15:05.488 position:50% align:center
With each sneeze,
your pillow moved

00:15:05.572 --> 00:15:07.365 position:50% align:center
further away from your cranium.

00:15:07.449 --> 00:15:09.451 position:50% align:center
Until, finally, you wound
up striking your head

00:15:09.534 --> 00:15:10.660 position:50% align:center
on the floor.

00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:12.162 position:50% align:center
The blow was enough
to burst several

00:15:12.245 --> 00:15:14.456 position:50% align:center
blood vessels in your brain.

00:15:14.539 --> 00:15:16.750 position:50% align:center
And that was all she wrote.

00:15:16.833 --> 00:15:19.085 position:50% align:center
That's so unfair, though!

00:15:19.169 --> 00:15:21.421 position:50% align:center
What a lame way to go out!

00:15:22.172 --> 00:15:24.799 position:50% align:center
The beer bottles
from my drunk boss!

00:15:24.883 --> 00:15:27.302 position:50% align:center
Years and years of
my father's abuse!

00:15:27.385 --> 00:15:28.970 position:50% align:center
I managed to survive all of it!

00:15:29.054 --> 00:15:32.015 position:50% align:center
But you're saying I died
from sneezing in my sleep?

00:15:32.098 --> 00:15:33.808 position:50% align:center
That's the first thing
that's bothered him.

00:15:33.892 --> 00:15:35.852 position:50% align:center
Statistically, something had to.

00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:38.396 position:50% align:center
It does make sense if you
stop and think about it.

00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:40.106 position:50% align:center
You had a secret pride
in how tough you were,

00:15:40.190 --> 00:15:41.232 position:50% align:center
didn't you?

00:15:43.151 --> 00:15:45.987 position:50% align:center
[TAKEBAYASHI]
I apologize. I lost my control.

00:15:46.071 --> 00:15:47.614 position:50% align:center
It's back, though,
so please go on.

00:15:47.697 --> 00:15:48.865 position:50% align:center
[GAIN clears throat]

00:15:48.948 --> 00:15:50.533 position:50% align:center
The heart of the matter
at hand is the reason

00:15:50.617 --> 00:15:53.203 position:50% align:center
I brought you here,
so allow me to explain.

00:15:53.286 --> 00:15:55.163 position:50% align:center
However, it's a bit clichÃ©.

00:15:55.246 --> 00:15:56.373 position:50% align:center
Which would mean
you're sending me

00:15:56.456 --> 00:15:58.249 position:50% align:center
to another world for
a second chance!

00:15:58.333 --> 00:16:01.294 position:50% align:center
And am I getting reincarnated
and do I have a special mission?

00:16:01.378 --> 00:16:03.963 position:50% align:center
It's astounding how
fast this is going.

00:16:04.047 --> 00:16:05.965 position:50% align:center
[GAIN] Yes, you will
be going to a new world,

00:16:06.049 --> 00:16:07.842 position:50% align:center
but you won't be
starting from scratch.

00:16:07.926 --> 00:16:10.804 position:50% align:center
You'll be entering a body
I made just for the occasion.

00:16:10.887 --> 00:16:12.764 position:50% align:center
[LULUTIA] You'll be around
eight years old, though,

00:16:12.847 --> 00:16:15.642 position:50% align:center
so you could consider it
a type of reincarnation.

00:16:15.725 --> 00:16:17.477 position:50% align:center
[TAKEBAYASHI]
What? Eight?

00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:19.646 position:50% align:center
[GAIN]
As for your "special mission"...

00:16:19.729 --> 00:16:21.272 position:50% align:center
You honestly won't have one.

00:16:21.356 --> 00:16:22.691 position:50% align:center
Okay then.

00:16:22.774 --> 00:16:24.901 position:50% align:center
[KUFO] There are walls
separating your world from ours.

00:16:24.984 --> 00:16:27.362 position:50% align:center
When we finally send you
off on your merry way,

00:16:27.445 --> 00:16:30.573 position:50% align:center
we'll be making a hole
in that world-dividing wall.

00:16:30.657 --> 00:16:32.701 position:50% align:center
And when that happens,
we'll be able to send

00:16:32.784 --> 00:16:35.787 position:50% align:center
the magical power from
Earth right along with you.

00:16:35.870 --> 00:16:37.205 position:50% align:center
[TAKEBAYASHI]
Magical power?

00:16:37.288 --> 00:16:38.832 position:50% align:center
Yeah, unfortunately,
our world is running

00:16:38.915 --> 00:16:40.667 position:50% align:center
a little low on it these days.

00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:43.086 position:50% align:center
So you're in need of some
more of this power.

00:16:43.169 --> 00:16:46.006 position:50% align:center
Yes. The Earth happens to be
brimming with magic,

00:16:46.089 --> 00:16:47.549 position:50% align:center
but nobody uses it.

00:16:47.632 --> 00:16:50.677 position:50% align:center
Wow. I never would
have guessed that.

00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:52.595 position:50% align:center
Will I...

00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:54.472 position:50% align:center
Will I be able to use
magic when I arrive

00:16:54.556 --> 00:16:55.724 position:50% align:center
at this new world?

00:16:55.807 --> 00:16:57.392 position:50% align:center
--Oh, you bet!
--I'm surprised you have to ask!

00:16:57.475 --> 00:16:58.768 position:50% align:center
Oh! That's so cool!

00:17:00.353 --> 00:17:02.564 position:50% align:center
I mean, that's fine.

00:17:02.647 --> 00:17:04.649 position:50% align:center
I do believe we've
piqued his interest.

00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:06.526 position:50% align:center
Well, shall we go ahead
and make it so you can

00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:08.778 position:50% align:center
use all types of magic?

00:17:08.862 --> 00:17:11.322 position:50% align:center
I feel like I'd stand
out too much.

00:17:11.406 --> 00:17:12.741 position:50% align:center
[GROUP laughs]

00:17:12.824 --> 00:17:15.076 position:50% align:center
There's no denying it's
a rare trait to have.

00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.704 position:50% align:center
But it's not as big of a
deal as you might think.

00:17:17.787 --> 00:17:20.790 position:50% align:center
And besides, you'd be more
like a jack of all trades,

00:17:20.874 --> 00:17:22.375 position:50% align:center
master of none.

00:17:22.459 --> 00:17:24.336 position:50% align:center
I understand.

00:17:24.419 --> 00:17:26.296 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA] After that, they gave
me a lot of advice

00:17:26.379 --> 00:17:28.214 position:50% align:center
and explanations.

00:17:28.298 --> 00:17:30.008 position:50% align:center
This was around the
time I concocted my

00:17:30.091 --> 00:17:33.720 position:50% align:center
"dead grandparents told me
to find a new village" story.

00:17:33.803 --> 00:17:35.221 position:50% align:center
I had to be prepared.

00:17:35.305 --> 00:17:37.182 position:50% align:center
It's not like I could tell
people I came from Earth,

00:17:37.265 --> 00:17:38.266 position:50% align:center
after all.

00:17:43.730 --> 00:17:45.857 position:50% align:center
Your new life is about to start!

00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:48.651 position:50% align:center
I hope you've properly
braced yourself for this!

00:17:48.735 --> 00:17:51.529 position:50% align:center
Hey! Don't be so formal
and polite all of the time.

00:17:51.613 --> 00:17:54.324 position:50% align:center
This is your chance to live
the life you've always wanted.

00:17:54.407 --> 00:17:55.742 position:50% align:center
Um, I'll try.

00:17:55.825 --> 00:17:57.160 position:50% align:center
Thanks for looking out.

00:17:57.243 --> 00:17:59.454 position:50% align:center
Uh! I mean... Whatever.

00:17:59.537 --> 00:18:00.955 position:50% align:center
We'll always be
watching over you,

00:18:01.039 --> 00:18:02.248 position:50% align:center
no matter where you go!

00:18:02.332 --> 00:18:03.500 position:50% align:center
The church should
be your first stop

00:18:03.583 --> 00:18:05.377 position:50% align:center
as soon as you make
it to the town.

00:18:05.460 --> 00:18:07.545 position:50% align:center
You'll have an oracle skill,
so you can use it

00:18:07.629 --> 00:18:09.673 position:50% align:center
whenever you need
to communicate with us.

00:18:09.756 --> 00:18:10.757 position:50% align:center
Sure thing.

00:18:10.840 --> 00:18:12.425 position:50% align:center
I'll put it at the top
of my to-do list

00:18:12.509 --> 00:18:14.511 position:50% align:center
when I get to town.

00:18:14.594 --> 00:18:16.388 position:50% align:center
Guess this is goodbye
for now, though.

00:18:16.471 --> 00:18:19.057 position:50% align:center
Have a wonderful and
exhilarating time, darling!

00:18:21.810 --> 00:18:25.897 position:50% align:center
I'm so grateful for this
gift you've given!

00:18:25.980 --> 00:18:28.358 position:50% align:center
Well then, shall we?

00:18:28.441 --> 00:18:30.777 position:50% align:center
With our powers combined,
we open for you

00:18:30.860 --> 00:18:32.696 position:50% align:center
the gate to a new world!

00:18:32.779 --> 00:18:35.198 position:50% align:center
[LULUTIA] May you be swathed in
nothing but our blessings!

00:18:35.281 --> 00:18:37.492 position:50% align:center
[KUFO] And may light shine
on the journey ahead!

00:18:40.829 --> 00:18:42.914 position:50% align:center
[RYOMA]
Before I knew it, I was off.

00:18:51.297 --> 00:18:54.759 position:50% align:center
I was reborn in a new world,
just like they said.

00:18:54.843 --> 00:18:56.845 position:50% align:center
In an eight-year-old body.

00:18:56.928 --> 00:18:59.806 position:50% align:center
I found myself in a place
I'd come to know as Seilfall.

00:19:04.310 --> 00:19:06.187 position:50% align:center
I really am a little kid.

00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:13.653 position:50% align:center
I've made it to another world.

00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:17.782 position:50% align:center
The gods were gracious enough
to prepare a manual

00:19:17.866 --> 00:19:19.409 position:50% align:center
that would help me
weather the hardships

00:19:19.492 --> 00:19:21.828 position:50% align:center
my new life might throw at me.

00:19:21.911 --> 00:19:23.663 position:50% align:center
Check the last page
of this book.

00:19:23.747 --> 00:19:25.874 position:50% align:center
You'll find your
starting status.

00:19:25.957 --> 00:19:28.376 position:50% align:center
I suddenly feel like a
character in a video game!

00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:33.590 position:50% align:center
All of my stats involve
brute strength somehow.

00:19:33.673 --> 00:19:35.592 position:50% align:center
Ah. It's fine.

00:19:35.675 --> 00:19:37.927 position:50% align:center
I guess they integrated my
skills from my last life

00:19:38.011 --> 00:19:39.262 position:50% align:center
into this one.

00:19:51.566 --> 00:19:54.652 position:50% align:center
Okay, so I'm definitely strong,
but I'm in a kid's body.

00:19:54.736 --> 00:19:56.321 position:50% align:center
I'll just have to get
used to that.

00:19:58.114 --> 00:19:59.199 position:50% align:center
A slime!

00:20:01.993 --> 00:20:03.870 position:50% align:center
Let's see if it knows
any tricks!

00:20:03.953 --> 00:20:05.080 position:50% align:center
Shake, boy.

00:20:06.956 --> 00:20:08.333 position:50% align:center
That's too bad.

00:20:08.416 --> 00:20:10.335 position:50% align:center
Oh! Magic! Duh!

00:20:12.170 --> 00:20:14.214 position:50% align:center
How to use your magic.

00:20:14.297 --> 00:20:16.800 position:50% align:center
To make a monster obey
your every command,

00:20:16.883 --> 00:20:18.802 position:50% align:center
you need taming magic.

00:20:18.885 --> 00:20:20.595 position:50% align:center
Oh, okay! Let's see.

00:20:26.101 --> 00:20:28.144 position:50% align:center
Calm your heart and feel
the magic flowing

00:20:28.228 --> 00:20:30.772 position:50% align:center
from the soles of your feet
to the top of your head.

00:20:30.855 --> 00:20:31.898 position:50% align:center
Feel it.

00:20:33.483 --> 00:20:35.610 position:50% align:center
This is my magic!

00:20:37.612 --> 00:20:39.572 position:50% align:center
Once you feel it
coursing through you,

00:20:39.656 --> 00:20:42.659 position:50% align:center
envision that same energy
flowing out of your body.

00:21:06.891 --> 00:21:08.768 position:50% align:center
I decided to make
the Forest of Gana

00:21:08.852 --> 00:21:10.478 position:50% align:center
my new home in this world.

00:21:12.105 --> 00:21:13.398 position:50% align:center
Because of how much I worked,

00:21:13.481 --> 00:21:15.233 position:50% align:center
it was next to impossible
for me to devote

00:21:15.316 --> 00:21:17.318 position:50% align:center
any time to hobbies.

00:21:17.402 --> 00:21:20.697 position:50% align:center
I think that's what led me
to researching slimes.

00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:22.532 position:50% align:center
It took me three years,

00:21:22.615 --> 00:21:24.743 position:50% align:center
but the first people
I came into contact with

00:21:24.826 --> 00:21:27.412 position:50% align:center
in Seilfall were Reinhart
and his companions.

00:21:28.788 --> 00:21:30.999 position:50% align:center
Two whole weeks have passed
since my unexpected

00:21:31.082 --> 00:21:34.169 position:50% align:center
encounter with those guys.

00:21:34.252 --> 00:21:35.712 position:50% align:center
That's weird.

00:21:35.795 --> 00:21:39.132 position:50% align:center
If these numbers are right,
then there's 364 sticky slimes.

00:21:39.215 --> 00:21:43.011 position:50% align:center
Whoa. They multiply faster
than rabbits do!

00:21:43.094 --> 00:21:44.804 position:50% align:center
Once Reinhart and
his friends left,

